This paper proposes a convolutional blind denoising network for endoscopic images using Deep Image Prior (DIP) method and MobileNet. The paper focuses on image processing and computer vision techniques for medical imaging, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of deep learning models such as MobileNet and convolutional neural networks (CNNs) indicates that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.MM), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
